          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Paraventricular Nucleus</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 33232,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Preoptic Nucleus</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 33233,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Suprachiasmatic Nucleus</span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 33234,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Medial Geniculate Body</span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 45-year-old patient presents with a complaint of disrupted sleep patterns, difficulty falling asleep at night, and excessive daytime sleepiness. Upon, further evaluation, it is found that this patient&rsquo;s sleep-wake cycle is not synchronized with the environmental light-dark cycle. Which hypothalamic nucleus is most likely involved in the regulation of this patient&rsquo;s circadian rhythms?</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q6827690",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 33073,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        2
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ans. C) Suprachiasmatic Nucleus</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option C:&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Correct. The <strong>Supra-Chiasmatic Nucleus (SCN)</strong> is known as the body&#39;s &quot;<strong>Master Clock</strong>.&quot; It regulates <strong>circadian rhythms</strong>, including the <strong>sleep-wake cycle</strong>, and is directly influenced by <strong>environmental light-dark</strong> cues received via the <strong>retina</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Explanation:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option A:&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Incorrect</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">. The Para-Ventricular Nucleus of the <strong>hypothalamus</strong> primarily <strong>regulates</strong> the <strong>autonomic nervous system</strong> and the release of <strong>hormones</strong> from the <strong>pituitary gland</strong>, but it is not directly involved in regulating circadian rhythms.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option B:&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Incorrect</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">. The preoptic nucleus plays a key role in <strong>thermoregulation</strong> and is involved in <strong>sleep regulation</strong>, but it does not directly control circadian rhythms and synchronization with the light-dark cycle.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Option D:&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Incorrect</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">. The medial geniculate body is part of the <strong>thalamus</strong> involved in <strong>auditory processing</strong> and is not directly responsible for circadian rhythm regulation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Educational Objective:</span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">The objective is to understand the role of the <strong>suprachiasmatic nucleus</strong> in the <strong>regulation</strong> of <strong>circadian rhythms</strong> and its importance in maintaining <strong>synchronization</strong> with the <strong>environmental light-dark cycle</strong>.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/02/27/picture1.jpg\" style=\"height:514px; width:1000px\" /></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Refer:&nbsp;</span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Ganong&rsquo;s Review of Medical Physiology, 25<sup>th</sup> Edition, Pg No: 278</span></strong></span></span></p>",
